Hi Mike.  That was a manual sweep using a Duracell KP028 emergency radio/flashlight.  
The total session was about 30 seconds.   I highly recommend this unit to anyone 
interested in working with manual sweep.  It&#39;s comfortable in the hand, really easy to turn 
the dial, and comes in a twin-pack for about $30 (including shipping) from places like 
Amazon and eBay.   

I do own both the old and new Radio Shack models 12-469, and the old 12-470.  While I 
have gotten good results with all of them, for me, there is no comparison in message 
length and clarity that I have received using the Duracell, so it is my preferred &#39;sweep&#39; 
unit.

I also have a MiniBox, which is a unique creature, unlike any of the radios.  ;0)

Thanks so much for listening and the feedback!

Margaret

